  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.6.6`\r\n\r\n##### Description\r\n\r\nTransactions go 'missing', and nonces are reused. \r\n\r\n* happening from one \"from-address\"\r\n* Seems to occurs more often with increased concurrency (not sure) \r\n* 2-3 workers with RPC-connections at once against geth, so at least some paralellism involved\r\n* One instance of geth\r\n* `eth_sendTransaction` is used. \r\n\r\n> The last time it happened, I dont believe we were under \"heavy load\" but i'm not sure what quantify's heavy load.  i would say no more than 100 tx's behind.\r\n\r\nRunning with `--targetgaslimit 1000000 --cache 1024 --txpool.accountqueue 8192` on the cmd line\r\n\r\nTicket filed on behalf of a user. ",
