    "body": "My theory is that transactions are queued up internally, but after two hours removed from 'local' cache, and thus they become removed due to the general pool cleaning. \r\n\r\nThese would by default start cropping the pending/queued to the following sizes: \r\n\r\n``` \r\n--txpool.accountslots value  Minimum number of executable transaction slots guaranteed per account (default: 16)\r\n--txpool.accountqueue value  Maximum number of non-executable transaction slots permitted per account (default: 64)\r\n```\r\n",
